Wash and dry produce.

In a #small pot{}, combine @Jasmine Rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4 servings), and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, trim and thinly slice @Scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

== Pickled Cucumber ==

In a #medium bowl{}, combine half the @White Wine Vinegar{5%teaspoon} (you'll use the rest later), @Sugar{1/2%teaspoon} (1 tsp for 4 servings), and a pinch of @salt{}.

Trim ends from @Cucumber{1}. Using a #peeler{}, shave cucumber lengthwise into ribbons, rotating as you go, until you get to the seedy core; discard core. Stir cucumber ribbons into bowl with vinegar mixture.

Set aside, tossing occasionally, until ready to serve.

== Sautéed Cabbage and Carrots ==

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large nonstick pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @Red Cabbage and Carrot Mix{4%ounce}; cook, stirring, until just tender, ~{1%minute}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Transfer to a #plate{}.

== Umami Ginger Turkey ==

Heat a drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites; cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Add @Ground Turkey{10%ounce} and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Stir in half the @Sesame Seeds{1%tablespoon} (save the rest for serving) and remaining vinegar. Cook for ~{30%seconds}, then stir in @Umami Ginger Sauce{4%ounce}.

Bring to a simmer, then immediately turn off heat. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> Simply cook through this step as instructed, swapping in beef or turkey for pork.

== Sriracha Crema ==

While pork cooks, in a #small bowl{}, combine @Sour Cream{3%tablespoon} with @Sriracha{1%teaspoon} to taste. Stir in water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with @salt{}.

== Assembly ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @Butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Divide rice between #bowls{}; top with pork, cabbage and carrots, and pickled cucumber (draining first). Drizzle with Sriracha crema. Garnish with scallion greens and as many remaining sesame seeds as you like. Serve.

> Ground Turkey is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.